			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Us</strong></p>
<p>
<br />
InVenture helps people throughout the developing world improve their finances, build credit scores and access financial services with technology We&rsquo;ve got real traction in some of the world&rsquo;s fastest growing markets, have great investors like Chris Sacca &amp; Google Ventures, and are ramping into high-growth mode. Together, we&rsquo;re building a life-changing accounting tool and large-scale credit scoring/analytics platform for massive markets and are looking for talented, challenge-driven individuals to join us.</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>You</strong></p>
<p>
<br />
You&rsquo;re a smart, experienced software developer, motivated by engineering great products. In this role you&rsquo;ll be developing core back-end components and larger features, as well as contributing to the core architecture of the system and data-driven scrum on growth funnels. Creating a global credit scoring platform involves solving problems that are both conceptually and technically hard, so you&rsquo;ll need a mix of experience including engineering and scaling for a high-volume web platform and working with big data systems and algorithms in areas such as machine learning and data mining.<br />
We&#39;re still small, so this is an opportunity to join the team early and have a big impact on what we&rsquo;re creating. We&rsquo;re looking for someone who cares passionately about user experience, is excited by growth, welcomes feedback, and wants to help build a great company as well as powerful software.</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
You&#39;ve used Java in a commercial environment and you&#39;re very knowledgeable about the common frameworks and libraries</li>
<li>
You have experience with a big data company that has seen fast growth or high volume</li>
<li>
You&rsquo;re experienced across multiple programming languages and have grown and managed a team; familiar with agile</li>
<li>
You can go beyond coding of individual components into architecture and product design: you&rsquo;ve worked on a large-scale service where you&rsquo;ve had to figure out architectural, scaling and infrastructure issues.</li>
<li>
You can talk about examples where you&rsquo;ve dealt with conceptually difficult product issues, tricky technical work and significant performance challenges</li>
<li>
Strong academic background in computer science or similarly mathematical/scientific discipline</li>
<li>
Comfortable crafting complex queries in MySQL.</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Bonus Points</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Entrepreneurial experience. You&rsquo;ve built something from scratch, know how to work independently and can be effective above all else</li>
<li>
Specific experience with recommender systems, machine learning, information retrieval, SMS and VOIP technology</li>
<li>
Experience building and leading a team</li>
<li>
Passion for increasing access to financial services and literacy</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Compensation</strong></p>
<p>
<br />
Competitive base salary, health benefits, stock options and many happy hours.</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Personality</strong></p>
<p>
<br />
Most importantly, you&rsquo;re a nice person, with a sense of humor. We work pretty hard and we all need to get along. You&rsquo;re a logical thinker who is also creative. You&rsquo;re objective, and embrace critique. And you&rsquo;re an experimenter - nothing here is static.</p>
<p>
<br />
<em><strong>Does that sound awesome? Then we can&#39;t wait to meet you.</strong></em></p>
